Description: The oak wilt range is a 20 mile buffer around all confirmed oak wilt points in Minnesota, unless confirmed as eradicated for 5 years by DNR staff. DNR data in Minnesota and Wisconsin indicates the risk of wounded oaks being infected overland by oak wilt is significant within 20 miles of known oak wilt.
